OL,3,CGuernsey man living in car calls
OL,4,Cisland's homelessness problem 'awful'
OL,6,F"Private rental costs are phenomenally
OL,7,Fhigh almost compared to any other
OL,8,Fjurisdiction on the planet.
OL,10,F"The lowest earning quarter of people
OL,11,Fon the island are paying up to 78% of
OL,12,Ftheir income on rent. That is patently
OL,13,Funsustainable."
OL,15,FMr Roberts says At Home in Guernsey is
OL,16,Fworking to secure the safety of people
OL,17,Fon low incomes in the short term by
OL,18,Fhelping people maximise the amount of
OL,19,Fgovernment support they can receive
OL,20,Fand working to maintain tenancy
OL,21,Fagreements.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G8/12
